      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) or equivalent order-of-accuracy test demonstrating spatial and temporal convergence consistent with nominal scheme order.",
      "rationale": "MMS applied to incompressible Navier-Stokes solver kernel; observed spatial order 1.97 (nominal 2nd order FVM). Temporal convergence verified with fixed CFL sweep. Achieves gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed on three systematically refined meshes; GCI on QOI (hemolysis index) must be below 5% at the finest mesh level.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study performed (coarse 4.1 M, medium 9.8 M, fine 22.3 M cells). GCI on hemolysis index at design point: 2.1%. Richardson extrapolation applied. Exceeds gradation 2 requirement; gradation 3 awarded due to asymptotic convergence confirmation."
    },
